[1] Bluetongue - Spain: (Basque Country), BTV-1, ovine, OIE
Date: Thu 8 Nov 2007
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly
disease information 2007; 20(45) [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/wahid-prod/public.php?page=weekly_report_index&admin=0>


Bluetongue, Spain
-----------------
Information received on (and dated) 6 Nov 2007 from Dr Lucio Ignacio
Carbajo Goni, Deputy Director General for Animal Health, Directorate:
General for Livestock, Ministry of Agriculture, Fisheries and Food,
Madrid, Spain

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Start date: 25 Oct 2007
Date of confirmation of event: 2 Nov 2007
Report date: 6 Nov 2007
Date submitted to OIE: 6 Nov 2007
Reason for notification: 1st occurrence of a listed disease
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: bluetongue virus, serotype 1
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (advanced)
Report pertains to: defined zone within the country

New outbreaks
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1 (LA 2007/1079): Oiartzun (Basque Country)
Date of start of outbreak: 25 Oct 2007
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not submitted)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals
Species: sheep
Susceptible: 130
Cases: 3
Deaths: 3
Destroyed: 0
Slaughtered: 0

Outbreak statistics
Species: sheep
Apparent morbidity rate: 2.31 percent
Apparent mortality rate: 2.31 percent
Apparent case fatality rate: 100 percent
Proportion susceptible removed*: 2.31 percent
* Removed from the susceptible population either through death,
destruction, or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Diagnostic test results:
Laboratory name and type: Central Veterinary Laboratory (Algete)
(National laboratory)
Species Sheep
Test: prueba ELISA de deteccion de anticuerpos [ELISA test for
detection of antibodies)
Test date: 29 Oct 2007
Result: positive

Species: sheep
Test PCR (polymerase chain reaction)
Test date: 2 Nov 2007
Result: positive

